<subSubSection pageId="100" pageNumber="101" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="100.[151,1437,150,717]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,438,464]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Remarks</emphasis>
. We tentatively follow 
<bibRefCitation author="Hendrickx, M. E." box="[569,770,438,464]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" pagination="287 - 290" refId="ref73236" refString="Hendrickx, M. E. (1993) Distribution of Petrolisthes lewisi (Crustacea: Porcellanidae) in the eastern tropical Pacific. Revista de Biologia Tropical, 41 (2), 287 - 290." type="journal article" year="1993">Hendrickx (1993)</bibRefCitation>
, who synonymised the two subspecies of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Glassell" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[1235,1327,438,464]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lewisi">
<emphasis box="[1235,1327,438,464]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">P. lewisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Haig, J." box="[186,324,474,501]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" pagination="1 - 440" refId="ref72816" refString="Haig, J. (1960) The Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Anomura) of the Eastern Pacific. Allan Hancock Pacific Expedition, 24, 1 - 440." type="journal article" year="1960">Haig (1960)</bibRefCitation>
, based on some differences in the armature of the P1 carpus, viz. 
<taxonomicName authority="lewisi" box="[1054,1218,474,500]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="lewisi" subSpecies="lewisi">
<emphasis box="[1054,1218,474,500]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">P. lewisi lewisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or “northern form” (
<collectingCountry box="[159,248,510,537]" name="Mexico" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Mexico</collectingCountry>
) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haig" authorityYear="1960" box="[309,511,510,536]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="lewisi" subSpecies="austrinus">
<emphasis box="[309,511,510,536]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">P. lewisi austrinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or “southern form” (
<collectingCountry box="[744,861,510,536]" name="Nicaragua" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Nicaragua</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[895,990,510,536]" name="Ecuador" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, but with some records from the Gulf of California). The sympatric occurrence of both subspecies in the Gulf of California is at least suspicious, although 
<bibRefCitation author="Hendrickx, M. E." box="[151,352,582,608]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" pagination="287 - 290" refId="ref73236" refString="Hendrickx, M. E. (1993) Distribution of Petrolisthes lewisi (Crustacea: Porcellanidae) in the eastern tropical Pacific. Revista de Biologia Tropical, 41 (2), 287 - 290." type="journal article" year="1993">Hendrickx (1993)</bibRefCitation>
found the differentianting character used by 
<bibRefCitation author="Haig, J." box="[863,1000,582,609]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" pagination="1 - 440" refId="ref72816" refString="Haig, J. (1960) The Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Anomura) of the Eastern Pacific. Allan Hancock Pacific Expedition, 24, 1 - 440." type="journal article" year="1960">Haig (1960)</bibRefCitation>
not valid. Nevertheless, we feel that a combined morphological-molecular study of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Glassell" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[660,753,618,644]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lewisi">
<emphasis box="[660,753,618,644]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">P. lewisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is needed to make a final conclusion on this issue. In life, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Glassell" baseAuthorityYear="1936" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lewisi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">P. lewisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be relatively easily recognised by the orange-brown carapace and much darker P1, as exemplified by the illustrated specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[444,554,690,716]" name="Colombia" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Colombia</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[570,654,690,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 61" captionStartId="99.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-19@99.[179,1407,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="99" captionText="FIGURE 61. Petrolisthes lewisi (Glassell, 1936): A, B, extra-limital specimen, male (cl 5.7 mm, cw 5.9 mm) from Bahía Málaga, Colombia (CRBM-UV-cr:2019-103), dorsal (A) and ventral (B) views [photographs by AA]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5532359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5532359/files/figure.png" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
